{"name":"Mathlib.Topology.UniformSpace.Compact","instances":[],"imports":["Init","Mathlib.Topology.UniformSpace.UniformConvergence","Mathlib.Topology.UniformSpace.Equicontinuity","Mathlib.Topology.Separation","Mathlib.Topology.Support"],"declarations":[{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Topology/UniformSpace/Compact.lean#L269-L273","name":"CompactSpace.uniformEquicontinuous_of_equicontinuous","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Topology/UniformSpace/Compact.html#CompactSpace.uniformEquicontinuous_of_equicontinuous","doc":"An equicontinuous family of functions defined on a compact uniform space is automatically\nuniformly equicontinuous. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Topology/UniformSpace/Compact.lean#L260-L262","name":"Continuous.tendstoUniformly","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Topology/UniformSpace/Compact.html#Continuous.tendstoUniformly","doc":"A continuous family of functions `α → β → γ` tends uniformly to its value at `x` if `α` is\nlocally compact and `β` is compact. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Topology/UniformSpace/Compact.lean#L248-L255","name":"ContinuousOn.tendstoUniformly","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Topology/UniformSpace/Compact.html#ContinuousOn.tendstoUniformly","doc":"A family of functions `α → β → γ` tends uniformly to its value at `x` if `α` is locally compact,\n`β` is compact and `f` is continuous on `U × (univ : Set β)` for some neighborhood `U` of `x`. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Topology/UniformSpace/Compact.lean#L240-L242","name":"HasCompactMulSupport.uniformContinuous_of_continuous","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Topology/UniformSpace/Compact.html#HasCompactMulSupport.uniformContinuous_of_continuous","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Topology/UniformSpace/Compact.lean#L239-L239","name":"HasCompactSupport.uniformContinuous_of_continuous","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Topology/UniformSpace/Compact.html#HasCompactSupport.uniformContinuous_of_continuous","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Topology/UniformSpace/Compact.lean#L226-L235","name":"HasCompactMulSupport.is_one_at_infty","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Topology/UniformSpace/Compact.html#HasCompactMulSupport.is_one_at_infty","doc":"If `f` has compact multiplicative support, then `f` tends to 1 at infinity. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Topology/UniformSpace/Compact.lean#L225-L225","name":"HasCompactSupport.is_zero_at_infty","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Topology/UniformSpace/Compact.html#HasCompactSupport.is_zero_at_infty","doc":"If `f` has compact support, then `f` tends to zero at infinity."},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Topology/UniformSpace/Compact.lean#L207-L221","name":"Continuous.uniformContinuous_of_tendsto_cocompact","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Topology/UniformSpace/Compact.html#Continuous.uniformContinuous_of_tendsto_cocompact","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Topology/UniformSpace/Compact.lean#L192-L204","name":"IsCompact.uniformContinuousAt_of_continuousAt","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Topology/UniformSpace/Compact.html#IsCompact.uniformContinuousAt_of_continuousAt","doc":"If `s` is compact and `f` is continuous at all points of `s`, then `f` is\n\"uniformly continuous at the set `s`\", i.e. `f x` is close to `f y` whenever `x ∈ s` and `y` is\nclose to `x` (even if `y` is not itself in `s`, so this is a stronger assertion than\n`UniformContinuousOn s`). "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Topology/UniformSpace/Compact.lean#L180-L185","name":"IsCompact.uniformContinuousOn_of_continuous","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Topology/UniformSpace/Compact.html#IsCompact.uniformContinuousOn_of_continuous","doc":"Heine-Cantor: a continuous function on a compact set of a uniform space is uniformly\ncontinuous. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Topology/UniformSpace/Compact.lean#L170-L175","name":"CompactSpace.uniformContinuous_of_continuous","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Topology/UniformSpace/Compact.html#CompactSpace.uniformContinuous_of_continuous","doc":"Heine-Cantor: a continuous function on a compact uniform space is uniformly\ncontinuous. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Topology/UniformSpace/Compact.lean#L81-L160","name":"uniformSpaceOfCompactT2","kind":"def","docLink":"./Mathlib/Topology/UniformSpace/Compact.html#uniformSpaceOfCompactT2","doc":"The unique uniform structure inducing a given compact topological structure. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Topology/UniformSpace/Compact.lean#L71-L77","name":"unique_uniformity_of_compact","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Topology/UniformSpace/Compact.html#unique_uniformity_of_compact","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Topology/UniformSpace/Compact.lean#L67-L68","name":"compactSpace_uniformity","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Topology/UniformSpace/Compact.html#compactSpace_uniformity","doc":"On a compact uniform space, the topology determines the uniform structure, entourages are\nexactly the neighborhoods of the diagonal. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Topology/UniformSpace/Compact.lean#L53-L62","name":"nhdsSet_diagonal_eq_uniformity","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Topology/UniformSpace/Compact.html#nhdsSet_diagonal_eq_uniformity","doc":"On a compact uniform space, the topology determines the uniform structure, entourages are\nexactly the neighborhoods of the diagonal. "}]}